This morning I lost my world and the world's most special woman. I miss her more than words can even describe. There is an emptiness in my heart that only her spirit can fill and I pray that I will feel her by my side every single day until we meet again. I attribute my strength to her.. She held on when she lost the love of her life.. The one she was married to for 53 years. She smiled even though she lost a son just this year. She told everyone she loved them every single chance she got and she joked even when her strokes left her unable to speak properly. The smile that she had not only could light up a whole room but it most definitely lit up the entire nursing home. She was my great-grandmother but we were so close that I never knew it was possible that anyone could have the bond that we shared even 70 years a part. The pain I feel is almost unbearable but because of her strength I will power through it. The love and support I have received has been empowering and so special to me.. I love all of you so much and I am forever grateful for the prayers, texts and fan art my Lovatics have made me. Thank you.

Mimaw, I hope you are with Papa now.. I hate that I can't hear your voice but I love that you are no longer in pain. I love you so much and I miss you more than anyone could ever imagine. I'll miss your smile, your wittiness, painting your nails and your kisses. I really do love you more. Rest in peace and most importantly rest in the Lord. #RIPMimaw

I owe so much to this man and his team at CAST Centers. Thank you for saving my life and congrats on 14 years of sobriety Mike Bayer. If you know someone who is looking for help please go to CastCenters.com.

Here's a note from Mike:

„Éª„Éª„Éª

To all my friends,

Yesterday I celebrated my 14th year of sobriety. 14 years ago, isolated from my family and loved ones, I was in an incredibly dark place. I was hearing voices that weren't there, hadn't eaten for days, and spent every penny I had left. Like so many other people who are struggling, I was completely hopeless and empty. These are just some of the many negative effects of addiction. 

After having been to that hell and back, I want to share how energized and proud of my journey I am today. I learned that my purpose in life is to help others. In the last 14 years I have helped people from all walks of life find themselves: Those perceived to be on "top" and those at "rock bottom". It became increasingly clear to me that only the people at the "top" have access to the best treatment in the world. That just didn't seem right, so I started a company with the notion that everyone should have access to an outstanding level of care. 

CAST Centers, a company I founded 10 years ago in Venice, CA in my tiny studio apartment has now grown into a leading treatment center that provides the highest quality of individualized care. I am excited to announce that we are now accepting insurance. This allows us to continue to provide the same level of service and unique care that the company was founded on but for more people. If you know anyone that is in need, our door is always open. Thank you for joining me on my journey, and in helping others find the freedom to be their best selves.

Love,

Mike Bayer
